These are the minutes for the October 9th, 2014 SPI Board Meeting,
held at 20:00 UTC in #spi on irc.spi-inc.org.
[LOG](../../../logs/2014/2014-10-09-log.txt).


## President's Report

Bdale Garbee reported two personal news items, which together have consumed
most of his attention in recent weeks.  The first is that after 15+ months,
his new house built to replace the one lost in the Black Forest Fire of
2013 is done.  The second is that he has been lured out of early
retirement, and he is now an HP Fellow in the Office of the CTO, focusing
on open source strategy.


## Treasurer's report

Michael Schultheiss reported that the three past treasurer reports have
been reissued and the three remaining reports needed to catch us up have
all been submitted.  The three reports have been reissued in order to fix
arithmetic errors and to correct some travel expenses which were accidentally
assigned to the wrong project.

Michael met with Bradley M. Kuhn at FOSSETCON who offered his help to move
SPI over to the accounting system that Software Freedom Conservancy is
using based on ledger-cli.  Michael believes that this system will make it
easier to manage SPI's finances.

There are no outstanding tax filings or other filings due until 2015.


## Secretary's report

Martin Michlmayr stated he had not received any new resolutions for
consideration.  Martin updated the trademark page to add the Drizzle
trademark.


